%N A337216 Irregular triangle read by rows: a(n, j) gives the positive integer area A(n)_j corresponding to the nonrectangular triangles with sides (sqrt(x(n)_j), sqrt(y(n)_j), z(n)), with integers  1 <= x(n)_j <= y(n)_j <= z(n), that lead to primitive quartets (x(n)_j, y(n)_j, z(n), a(n, j)). Hence  x(n)_j = A336888(n, 2*j-1), y(n)_j = A336888(n, 2*j), for j = 1, 2, ..., A336889(n), and z(n) = A337215(n), for n >= 1.
